        "tooltips": [
          {
            "htmlId": "scenario4_tooltip1",
            "personStatement": "I've heard that when I add my work account to my mobile device, the only way for IT to remove work information is by clearing all the data on my phone, including photos taken from my last family holiday.",
            "businessStatement": "IT needs to remove company data on employees' personal phones and tablets if the device is lost, compromised or the employee leaves the organization.",
            "initialPosition": "mam-scenario4__tooltip1 scenario-tooltip--anchor",
            "style": "scenario--tooltip__pin text--white glyphicon glyphicon-pushpin",
            "position": "top-right",
            "type": "problem_start"
          },
          {
            "htmlId": "scenario4_tooltip2",
            "personStatement": "Because I don't want to lose my personal data, I may delay telling IT that I have lost my mobile device.",
            "businessStatement": "IT is under a lot of pressure from employees to retain their personal information when removing company data, which can be time-consuming.",
            "initialPosition": "mam-scenario4__tooltip2 scenario-tooltip--anchor",
            "style": "scenario--tooltip__pin text--white glyphicon glyphicon-pushpin",
            "position": "bottom-left",
            "type": "problem"
          },
          {
            "htmlId": "scenario4_tooltip3",
            "personStatement": "To protect my personal photos, I have to request a work phone from my employer and carry two phones with me to keep work and personal data separate.",
            "businessStatement": "Systems that allow IT to differentiate between company and personal data on employee's personal mobile devices are often complex and expensive to setup for smaller organizations.",
            "initialPosition": "mam-scenario4-tooltip3 scenario-tooltip--anchor",
            "style": "scenario--tooltip__pin text--white glyphicon glyphicon-pushpin",
            "position": "top-right",
            "type": "problem"
          },
          {
            "htmlId": "scenario4_tooltip4",
            "businessStatement": "Having their personal data protected makes employees more at ease with adding their work account into their personal device and will be more likely to report lost or compromised mobile device promptly.",
            "initialPosition": "mam-scenario4__tooltip4 scenario-tooltip--anchor",
            "style": "scenario--tooltip__pin text--white glyphicon glyphicon-pushpin",
            "position": "bottom-right",
            "type": "solution_start"
          },
          {
            "htmlId": "scenario4_tooltip5",
            "businessStatement": "When my IT admin chooses to remove company data from my phone, my personal data such as family photos are not lost.",
            "initialPosition": "mam-scenario4__tooltip5 scenario-tooltip--anchor",
            "style": "scenario--tooltip__pin text--white glyphicon glyphicon-pushpin",
            "position": "bottom-right",
            "type": "solution"
          },
          {
            "htmlId": "scenario4_tooltip6",
            "businessStatement": "Although the IT admin still has the option to remove all the data on the mobile phone, they now have the option to only wipe the company data.",
            "initialPosition": "mam-scenario4__tooltip6 scenario-tooltip--anchor",
            "style": "scenario--tooltip__pin text--white glyphicon glyphicon-pushpin",
            "position": "top-right",
            "type": "solution"
